==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛst|-ɛst]]

===Noun===
'''vest''' (''plural'' '''vests''')

#{{british}} A [[sleeveless]] garment, often with a low-cut neck, usually worn under a [[shirt]] or [[blouse]].
#{{US}} A sleeveless garment that [[button]]s down the front, worn over a [[shirt]], and often as part of a [[suit]].
#A protective sleeveless garment worn over outer clothing.

====Synonyms====
*(''garment worn under a shirt''): [[singlet]], [[tank top]] {{US}}, [[undershirt]] {{US}}
*(''garment worn over a shirt''): [[waistcoat]] {{british}}

====Derived terms====
*[[bulletproof vest]]
*[[life vest]]<!-- = life jacket -->

